Identification_Area.title: Cassini ISS Image Index Table for the Cruise to Saturn

Citation_Information.author_list: M. R. Showalter, R. S. French, M. W. Evans, M. K. Gordon, and M. S. Tiscareno
Citation_Information.description: This table describes the general properties of each Cassini ISS image.

File.comment: This table describes the general properties of each Cassini ISS image.

Table_Character.description:
This version of the Cassini ISS image index for PDS3 volumes COISS_1001 to COISS_1009 has been edited by the PDS Ring-Moon Systems Node for compliance with PDS3 standards. Invalid rows have been edited so they obey the specified DATA_TYPE and can therefore be read more easily by software. For example, where a numeric column contained 'NULL', that value has been replaced by '-1.e32' and, in the label, a numeric value of -1.e32 has been identified as the NULL_CONSTANT or NOT_APPLICABLE_CONSTANT.
Note that NULL_CONSTANT identifies values that could be known but are not, whereas NOT_APPLICABLE_CONSTANT refers to values that are undefined. An example of the former would be a missing value of SC_SUN_POSITION_VECTOR; an example of the latter would be a value of LOWER_LEFT_LATITUDE in an image where the lower left corner does not intercept the target body.
Note: This file was obtained from the PDS Ring-Moon Systems Node at this URL: https://pds-rings.seti.org/viewmaster/metadata/COISS_1xxx/COISS_1999/COISS_1999_index.tab It was downloaded on July 30, 2019. Two additional, leading columns, containing the image LID and PDS4 raw image file path, have been pre-pended to each record; the remainder of each record is unchanged.

Field_Character.name: Image LID
Field_Character.description: The LID for this image.

Field_Character.name: File Name
Field_Character.description: The name of the associated raw image file.

Field_Character.name: PDS3_FILE_NAME
Field_Character.description: The PDS3 name of the associated raw image file.

Field_Character.name: FILE_SPECIFICATION_NAME
Field_Character.description: Path name locating images in DATA directory on PDS3 data set volumes.

Field_Character.name: VOLUME_ID
Field_Character.description: The PDS3 volume on which the product is stored.

Field_Character.name: ANTIBLOOMING_STATE_FLAG
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether antiblooming was used for this image.

Field_Character.name: BIAS_STRIP_MEAN
Field_Character.description: Mean value of the overclocked pixel values from all lines except the first and last. Not affected by light or dark current.

Field_Character.name: CALIBRATION_LAMP_STATE_FLAG
Field_Character.description: Indicates whether calibration lamp was used for this image. (ISSNA has none, so it's always 'N/A')

Field_Character.name: COMMAND_FILE_NAME
Field_Character.description: The name of the IOI file containing the observation description for this product - sent from the ISS Team Lead to IO.

Field_Character.name: COMMAND_SEQUENCE_NUMBER
Field_Character.description: Numeric identifier for a sequence of commands sent to the spacecraft. Also known as 'trigger number'. (Comes from the TRIGGER_NUMBER keyword in the IOI file.) Note that 1-12 are reserved for IO use and 8 is reserved for OpNav.

Field_Character.name: DARK_STRIP_MEAN
Field_Character.description: Mean value of the extended pixel values from all lines except the first and last. Not affected by light, but by dark current and Dark Band problem.

Field_Character.name: DATA_CONVERSION_TYPE
Field_Character.description: The method of conversion used to convert image from 12 to 8 bits selected for this image. '12BIT' = no conversion 'TABLE' = conversion by look-up table '8LSB' = keep only the 8 least significant bits

Field_Character.name: DATA_SET_ID
Field_Character.description: PDS/Cassini-supplied name for this data set.

Field_Character.name: DELAYED_READOUT_FLAG
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether the image may have waited on the CCD while the other camera was performing a readout.

Field_Character.name: DESCRIPTION
Field_Character.description: Descriptive comment up to 255 characters. Populated by IO telemetry processing, validation and reconciliation software to describe known limitations of this product.

Field_Character.name: DETECTOR_TEMPERATURE
Field_Character.description: Temperature of CCD in Celsius degrees.

Field_Character.name: EARTH_RECEIVED_START_TIME
Field_Character.description: Earth Received time of the earliest record containing valid data for this image (UTC).

Field_Character.name: EARTH_RECEIVED_STOP_TIME
Field_Character.description: Earth Received time of the latest record containing valid data for this image (UTC).

Field_Character.name: ELECTRONICS_BIAS
Field_Character.description: Commanded electronics bias to ensure that all DN values are greater than zero. (Comes from the VIDEO_OFFSET keyword in the IOI file.)

Field_Character.name: EXPECTED_MAXIMUM
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, represents the ratio of the expected maximum DN in the image to the VALID_MAXIMUM (full well DN). Second, represents the ratio of the expected maximum DN in the image to the VALID_MAXIMUM (maxDN).

Field_Character.name: EXPECTED_PACKETS
Field_Character.description: This keyword provides the total number of packets expected to be stored on the SSR for this image. To convert to volume in bits, multiply this value by 7616 bits/packet. (Comes from the EXPECTED_PACKETS keyword in the IOI file.)

Field_Character.name: EXPOSURE_DURATION
Field_Character.description: Exposure duration for the image in milliseconds. 63 distinct values from 0 to 1200000. (See table in Appendix A.) -999.0 if extended header is unavailable

Field_Character.name: FILTER_NAME
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, filters used on filter wheel 1. Second, filters used on filter wheel 2.

Field_Character.name: FILTER_TEMPERATURE
Field_Character.description: Temperature of the filter wheels.

Field_Character.name: FLIGHT_SOFTWARE_VERSION_ID
Field_Character.description: Indicates version of instrument flight software used to acquire image.

Field_Character.name: GAIN_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: The electronics gain setting selected for this image, given in units of electrons per DN. (This is an approximate value so both cameras can use the same set of values.)

Field_Character.name: IMAGE_MID_TIME
Field_Character.description: Exposure mid-time calculated from spacecraft clock using both the coarse (seconds) and fine (subRTI) counters (UTC). (A subRTI is approximately 4 msec (1/256 second)). This value is calculated from the SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT - (EXPOSURE_DURATION/ 2) then converted to UTC. When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the IMAGE_MID_TIME = START_TIME = STOP_TIME, and all three represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image.

Field_Character.name: IMAGE_NUMBER
Field_Character.description: The seconds portion of the spacecraft clock at shutter close.

Field_Character.name: IMAGE_OBSERVATION_TYPE
Field_Character.description: A multi-valued list describing the purpose(s) of this image, for example, OPNAV, science, calibration, engineering and/or support imaging. (Comes from the IMAGE_OBSERVATION_TYPE_* keywords in the IOI file parameter set description.) This list can contain up to five values where the purposes of the image are identified. More than one value may be specified.

Field_Character.name: IMAGE_TIME
Field_Character.description: Time of shutter close calculated from spacecraft clock using both the coarse (seconds) and fine (subRTI) counters (UTC). (A subRTI is approximately 4 msec (1/256 second)). When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the IMAGE_TIME = START_TIME = STOP_TIME, and all three represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_DATA_RATE
Field_Character.description: The rate at which data was transferred out of instrument. -999.0 if channelized data and extended header are unavailable.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_HOST_NAME
Field_Character.description: Name of the spacecraft upon which this instrument resides.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_ID
Field_Character.description: Indicator of which camera took this image.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: The summation mode used for this image.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_NAME
Field_Character.description: Name of the CASSINI Instrument which acquired the image data.

Field_Character.name: INST_CMPRS_PARAM
Field_Character.description: 4-valued array. First, the lossy compression MALGO (algorithm) parameter. MALGO. Second, the lossy compression TB (block type) parameter. TB. Third, the lossy compression group-of-blocks (number of blocks per group) parameter. GOB. Fouth, the lossy compression the compression rate parameter (quantization factor). QF.

Field_Character.name: INST_CMPRS_RATE
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, the expected average number of bits and comes from the BITS_PER_PIXEL keyword in the IOI file. Second, the actual average number of bits and is calculated during telemetry processing.

Field_Character.name: INST_CMPRS_RATIO
Field_Character.description: Ratio of expected image size to size of image received. (Calculation of this value does not include data outages due to truncated readouts or data lost in transmission.)

Field_Character.name: INST_CMPRS_TYPE
Field_Character.description: Compression type used for the image.

Field_Character.name: LIGHT_FLOOD_STATE_FLAG
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether Light Flood was used just prior to taking this image.

Field_Character.name: METHOD_DESC
Field_Character.description: This keyword describes the information and/or algorithm used to calculate the I/F value used by the ISS team to determine the EXPOSURE_DURATION. (Limited to char(75)). (Comes from the METHOD_DESC keyword in the IOI file.)

Field_Character.name: MISSING_LINES
Field_Character.description: For non-lossy compressed data only, number of missing or incomplete image lines. For all data, including lossy compressed images, when data is missing, the missing pixel values are replaced by 0. 'N/A' for lossy compressed data.

Field_Character.name: MISSING_PACKET_FLAG
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether consecutive packets were received. If set to 'YES', this flag indicates that packets needed to construct a complete image were missing. If set to 'NO', all consecutive packets were received. However, data may be missing at the beginning or end of the image. In this case, missing data would be reflected in the MISSING_LINES keyword for non-lossy data, and through visual inspection for lossy compressed data.

Field_Character.name: MISSION_NAME
Field_Character.description: Mission name associated with this image.

Field_Character.name: MISSION_PHASE_NAME
Field_Character.description: Mission phase of which this image is a part.

Field_Character.name: OBSERVATION_ID
Field_Character.description: Name of observation of which this image is a part.

Field_Character.name: OPTICS_TEMPERATURE
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, temperature of front optics in Celsius degrees. Note that there is no rear optics temperature for the WAC camera, so when INSTRUMENT_ID = ISSWA, the second element of the array will always be -999.0. (-999.0, -999.0) if the extended header is unavailable. Second, temperature of rear optics in Celsius degrees. Note that there is no rear optics temperature for the WAC camera, so when INSTRUMENT_ID = ISSWA, the second element of the array will always be -999.0. (-999.0, -999.0) if the extended header is unavailable.

Field_Character.name: ORDER_NUMBER
Field_Character.description: Identifier provided by Team Lead for this image which is unique within the IOI file. This value will not be unique for parameter sets described in the IOI file with ITERATION_COUNT > 1 or with LOOP_COUNT > 1

Field_Character.name: PARALLEL_CLOCK_VOLTAGE_INDEX
Field_Character.description: Commanded parallel clock voltage index. Controls clocking frequency. (Comes from the PC_VOLTAGE keyword in the IOI file.)

Field_Character.name: PREPARE_CYCLE_INDEX
Field_Character.description: The element number within the Prepare Cycle table selected for this image. (see Appendix B tables)

Field_Character.name: PRODUCT_CREATION_TIME
Field_Character.description: Time of creation of this image on the ground (Pacific local time).

Field_Character.name: PRODUCT_ID
Field_Character.description: Unique identifier for each image commanded. Required by PDS/Cassini. The PRODUCT_ID will be constructed: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_CNT_PARTITION'_' ISPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT, where I is 'N' if the INSTRUMENT_ID is 'ISSNA', and I is 'W' if the INSTRUMENT_ID is 'ISSWA'.

Field_Character.name: PRODUCT_VERSION_TYPE
Field_Character.description: Identifies the version of an individual data product. Always 'FINAL' for products archived with PDS/Cassini. 'PRELIMINARY' indicates additional processing is underway at IO/MIPL, for instance, to recover additional telemetry if possible.

Field_Character.name: READOUT_CYCLE_INDEX
Field_Character.description: The element number within the Readout Cycle table selected for this image. (see Appendix B tables)

Field_Character.name: RECEIVED_PACKETS
Field_Character.description: This keyword provides the actual number of packets received from the SSR for this image. To convert to volume in bits, multiply this value by 7616 bits/packet. This value reflects data received. In the event the image is incomplete due to an outage in the transmission, this field will not be an accurate indicator of actual volume on the SSR.

Field_Character.name: SENSOR_HEAD_ELEC_TEMPERATURE
Field_Character.description: Temperature of the sensor head electronics.

Field_Character.name: SEQUENCE_ID
Field_Character.description: Identifies the segment associated with this image. Note that this keyword does not come from the IOI file. Ex: 'C22', 'S19'

Field_Character.name: SEQUENCE_NUMBER
Field_Character.description: Indicates the order in which this image was expected to be taken within the given observation (OBSERVATION_ID).

Field_Character.name: SEQUENCE_TITLE
Field_Character.description: The name assigned by the Team Lead for the activity of which this image is a part. Comes from the SEQUENCE_TITLE keyword in the IOI file. Limited to 30 characters. Example = ???.

Field_Character.name: SHUTTER_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether this exposure was part of a joint observation with the other ISS camera.

Field_Character.name: SHUTTER_STATE_ID
Field_Character.description: Indicator of whether the shutter was enabled during the exposure.

Field_Character.name: SOFTWARE_VERSION_ID
Field_Character.description: Ground software version used to generate this image.

Field_Character.name: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_CNT_PARTITION
Field_Character.description: Indicates the clock partition active for the SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_START_COUNT and SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT elements. Remains at '1' unless the spacecraft clock rolls over or is reset.

Field_Character.name: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_START_COUNT
Field_Character.description: The seconds and subRTI portions of the spacecraft clock at shutter open. Calculated from spacecraft clock of shutter close less the exposure duration. When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_START_COUNT = SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT, and both represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image. EX: '832898283.123'

Field_Character.name: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT
Field_Character.description: The seconds and subRTI portions of the spacecraft clock at shutter close. (A subRTI is approximately 4 msec (1/256 second)). When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STA RT_COUNT = SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT, and both represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image. EX: '832898284.456'

Field_Character.name: START_TIME
Field_Character.description: Time of shutter open. Calculated from spacecraft clock of shutter close less the exposure duration. Expressed in UTC format, and includes subRTI resolution. (A subRTI is approximately 4 msec (1/256 second)). When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the START_TIME = STOP_TIME, and both represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image. EX: 1996-158T05:53:34.000Z

Field_Character.name: STOP_TIME
Field_Character.description: Time of shutter close from spacecraft clock (UTC). Identical to IMAGE_TIME. Includes subRTI resolution. (A subRTI is approximately 4 msec (1/256 second)). When the shutter was inhibited (ie SHUTTER_STATE_ID='DISABLED'), the START_TIME = STOP_TIME, and both represent the start of the exposure window during the prepare cycle of the image. EX: 1996-158T05:53:34.000Z

Field_Character.name: TARGET_DESC
Field_Character.description: The name of the intended target for which the exposure was calculated/selected in the given image. May include calibration type information. Limited to 75 characters. (Comes from the TARGET_DESC keyword in the IOI file.)

Field_Character.name: TARGET_NAME
Field_Character.description: Identifies a target. The target may be a planet, satellite, ring, region, feature, asteroid or comet.

Field_Character.name: TELEMETRY_FORMAT_ID
Field_Character.description: The telemetry mode in effect when sending data from the instrument to the spacecraft computer.

Field_Character.name: VALID_MAXIMUM
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, indicates the minimum full well saturation level of the instrument, which is a function of INSTRUMENT_MODE_ID, INSTRUMENT_ID, and GAIN_MODE_ID, expressed as a DN value. This may exceed 4095. Second, indicates the maximum DN saturation level for the signal returned by the A/D converter. Valid values are 255 and 4095. See Appendix B tables

Field_Character.name: CENTRAL_BODY_DISTANCE
Field_Character.description: Distance from spacecraft to center of primary body.

Field_Character.name: COORDINATE_SYSTEM_NAME
Field_Character.description: The full name of the coordinate system to which the state vectors are referenced.

Field_Character.name: DECLINATION
Field_Character.description: Declination of camera optic axis.

Field_Character.name: EMISSION_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Emission angle at aimpoint on target.

Field_Character.name: INCIDENCE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Incidence angle at aimpoint on target.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_LEFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of lower-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_LEFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of lower-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_RIGHT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of lower-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_RIGHT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of lower-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: MAXIMUM_RING_RADIUS
Field_Character.description: Maximum ringplane radius in image.

Field_Character.name: MINIMUM_RING_RADIUS
Field_Character.description: Minimum ringplane radius in image.

Field_Character.name: NORTH_AZIMUTH_CLOCK_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Direction of the northward-pointing azimuth at the aimpoint on the target body, measured clockwise.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_NORTH_CLOCK_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Angle, about optic axis, between 'up' image direction and target pole projected onto image plane, measured clockwise.

Field_Character.name: PHASE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Phase angle at subspacecraft point on target.

Field_Character.name: PIXEL_SCALE
Field_Character.description: Size of one pixel at subspacecraft point on target body.

Field_Character.name: PLANET_CENTER
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, Line of target body center. Second, Sample of target body center.

Field_Character.name: RIGHT_ASCENSION
Field_Character.description: Right ascension of camera optic axis.

Field_Character.name: RING_CENTER_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude at aimpoint on ring

Field_Character.name: RING_CENTER_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude at aimpoint on ring

Field_Character.name: RING_EMISSION_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Emission angle relative to target ring northward- pointing normal at aimpoint.

Field_Character.name: RING_INCIDENCE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Incidence angle relative to target ring northward- pointing normal at aimpoint.

Field_Character.name: RINGS_FLAG
Field_Character.description: If any part of the A, B, C, D, E, F, or G ring is visible in the image, this quantity is 'YES'; 'NO' otherwise.

Field_Character.name: SC_PLANET_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to primary planet center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_PLANET_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the velocity vector of primary planet relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SC_SUN_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to sun center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_SUN_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the velocity vector of sun relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SC_TARGET_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to target center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_TARGET_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X, Y, Z components of the velocity vector of the target relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SPICE_PRODUCT_ID
Field_Character.description: The names of the SPICE files used in processing the data.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SOLAR_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of subsolar point on target; Ring_Subsolar_Latitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SOLAR_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of subsolar point on target; Ring_Subsolar_Longitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SPACECRAFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of subspacecraft point on target; Ring_Subspacecraft_Latitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SPACECRAFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of subspacecraft point on target; Ring_Subspacecraft_Longitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: CENTER_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude at aimpoint on target (or Ring_Aimpoint_Latitude if target is a ring).

Field_Character.name: CENTER_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude at aimpoint on target (or Ring_Aimpoint_Longitude if target is a ring).

Field_Character.name: TARGET_DISTANCE
Field_Character.description: Distance from the spacecraft to the center of the target.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_EASTERNMOST_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: Easternmost longitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_NORTHERNMOST_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Northernmost latitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_SOUTHERNMOST_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Southernmost latitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_WESTERNMOST_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: Westernmost longitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TWIST_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Twist angle of optic axis.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_LIST
Field_Character.description: Name of each body visible in the image. A body is included if any part of its limb is not hidden by another body. Bodies may be obscured by rings.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_LEFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of upper-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_LEFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of upper-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_RIGHT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of upper-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_RIGHT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of upper-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: DATA_SET_NAME
Field_Character.description: The name given to the Cassini ISS EDR image data set.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_HOST_ID
Field_Character.description: Unique identifier for the host where the instrument is located.

Field_Character.name: PRODUCT_TYPE
Field_Character.description: Identifies the type of a data product within the data set.

Field_Character.name: STANDARD_DATA_PRODUCT_ID
Field_Character.description: Used to link a data product (file) to a standard data product (collection of similar files) described within software interface specification document for a particular data set.
